- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with a formal system (abstract rewrite system) and introduces a probabilistic extension to it. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely because the paper discusses a calculus (Lambda+) and transforms it into a probabilistic one. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with probability measures and their application to a set of execution traces. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possibility because the paper deals with a formal system and its probabilistic extension. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility because the paper introduces a probabilistic extension to a non-deterministic calculus.
